---
# Symphony-TS workflow contract. Copy to WORKFLOW.md and customize.
tracker:
  kind: linear
  # Right-click your Linear project → Copy URL; the slug is the trailing segment.
  project_slug: "your-project-slug"
  # Reads LINEAR_API_KEY from the environment when api_key is unset or "$LINEAR_API_KEY".
  api_key: $LINEAR_API_KEY
  # Symphony custom flow — set these up in Linear: Team Settings → Workflow.
  active_states: [Todo, In Progress, Rework, Merging]
  terminal_states: [Done, Closed, Canceled, Cancelled, Duplicate]
  # Note: "Human Review" is intentionally NOT active — it parks work for a human.

polling:
  interval_ms: 5000

workspace:
  # Single shared repo (local path or git URL); every ticket gets a worktree off it.
  repo: git@github.com:your-org/your-repo.git
  root: ~/code/symphony-workspaces
  branch_prefix: "symphony/"

hooks:
  # Runs once per new worktree. Install deps here.
  after_create: |
    if [ -f package.json ]; then npm ci || npm install; fi
  timeout_ms: 120000

agent:
  backend: claude-sdk        # claude-sdk | claude-cli | codex-cli | opencode-cli
  permission_mode: bypassPermissions   # full autonomy (high-trust)
  max_concurrent_agents: 5
  max_turns: 20
  # model: claude-opus-4-8   # optional override
  # max_budget_usd: 5        # optional per-turn budget cap (claude-sdk)

server:
  port: 4500                 # enables the dashboard at http://127.0.0.1:4500/
---

You are an autonomous engineer working on Linear issue {{ issue.identifier }} in an isolated git
worktree on branch `symphony/{{ issue.identifier }}`.

Title: {{ issue.title }}
{% if issue.description %}
{{ issue.description }}
{% else %}
(No description provided.)
{% endif %}

Your job:
1. Implement the change end-to-end. Keep edits scoped to this issue.
2. Run the project's build/tests/lints and make them pass before finishing.
3. Commit your work with a concise message, push the `symphony/{{ issue.identifier }}` branch,
   and open a pull request.
4. Move the Linear issue to its next workflow state using the `linear_graphql` tool
   (e.g. transition to "Human Review" or "Merging" per your team's process), and post a short
   comment summarizing what you did and linking the PR.
5. If you are blocked and genuinely need a human decision, say so explicitly and stop — do not guess.

You have a `linear_graphql` tool that runs raw Linear GraphQL queries/mutations with Symphony's
configured auth (use it for state transitions, comments, and PR metadata).
